WEBVTT

00:06.310 --> 00:08.138
[inhales deeply]

00:13.535 --> 00:17.060
[exhales]

00:17.104 --> 00:19.845
Welcome back to the land
of the living, Mr. Getty.

00:27.723 --> 00:29.768
What...?

00:29.812 --> 00:32.162
What happened?

00:32.206 --> 00:34.469
Just a little brush with death.

00:34.512 --> 00:37.167
You had us worried there
for a while.

00:37.211 --> 00:38.647
Oh.

00:38.690 --> 00:41.345
[groans softly]

00:41.389 --> 00:43.347
Is my wife here?

00:43.391 --> 00:45.610
No.

00:45.654 --> 00:48.831
I'm sorry, you haven't
had any visitors.

00:48.874 --> 00:51.268
Well...

00:51.312 --> 00:54.402
we have been having
some trouble lately.

00:56.230 --> 00:58.188
But you know what?

00:58.232 --> 01:00.625
Second chance on life.

01:00.669 --> 01:04.064
Maybe it's not too late
to turn things around.

01:04.107 --> 01:05.543
♪ Hey!

01:11.680 --> 01:15.423
[woman giggling]

01:15.466 --> 01:16.815
[man and woman chattering]

01:16.859 --> 01:18.165
[quietly]:
No, you wouldn't.

01:18.208 --> 01:20.080
[woman giggling]

01:20.123 --> 01:21.168
No.

01:21.211 --> 01:24.432
[woman laughs]

01:24.475 --> 01:25.737
[door unlocks]

01:25.781 --> 01:28.523
So, sorry to shag and run,
darling, but, uh,

01:28.566 --> 01:30.873
I'll see you
next time.

01:30.916 --> 01:32.440
All right.

01:32.483 --> 01:35.269
Ah. Lovely.

01:35.312 --> 01:38.489
♪ Aren't you really tired
of taking your clothes off ♪

01:38.533 --> 01:43.842
♪ Making people think
that you're so tough ♪

01:43.886 --> 01:45.148
♪ Hey!

01:45.192 --> 01:47.281
♪ Oh, oh

01:47.324 --> 01:49.196
♪ Give it up

01:52.373 --> 01:54.897
♪ Please...

01:54.940 --> 01:57.900
Who the hell
does he think he is?

01:57.943 --> 01:59.293
Lucifer Morningstar.

01:59.336 --> 02:01.338
You're serious?
That's his name?

02:01.382 --> 02:03.688
What kind of idiot
calls himself that?

02:03.732 --> 02:06.126
The kind who owns this place.

02:10.347 --> 02:12.262
Don't think I haven't noticed
you watching me.

02:12.306 --> 02:14.308
I know what
this is about.

02:14.351 --> 02:15.874
You do?

02:15.918 --> 02:17.441
Yes,

02:17.485 --> 02:18.921
and the answer is no.

02:18.964 --> 02:20.270
I will not sleep with you.

02:20.314 --> 02:21.924
Excuse me?

02:21.967 --> 02:24.318
It's not because you're a man.
It's just because...

02:24.361 --> 02:25.667
Well, I don't
find you attractive.

02:25.710 --> 02:27.321
But maybe I could

02:27.364 --> 02:30.367
introduce you to someone more,
you know, your league?

02:30.411 --> 02:32.021
There's a chubby fellow
over there.

02:32.064 --> 02:33.718
I'm sure he wouldn't mind giving
you a reach-around or something.

02:33.762 --> 02:36.460
I'm married... to a woman,
thank you very much.

02:36.504 --> 02:37.896
Oh. Does she know you're gay?

02:37.940 --> 02:39.289
My wife,

02:39.333 --> 02:43.119
who's the smartest
and funniest person I ever met,

02:43.163 --> 02:45.295
and the only woman
that I've ever loved,

02:45.339 --> 02:47.341
is sleeping with another man.

02:47.384 --> 02:51.910
A sleazy, arrogant,
womanizing piece of garbage.

02:51.954 --> 02:54.522
Well, then, why are you wasting
time trying to pick me up?

02:54.565 --> 02:56.524
You should be punishing him.

02:56.567 --> 02:58.134
Oh, don't worry.
I'm going to.

02:58.178 --> 02:59.309
Oh, are you? Great.

02:59.353 --> 03:00.832
What are you gonna do,
spoons to the eyes?

03:00.876 --> 03:02.007
Ants inside his urethra?

03:02.051 --> 03:04.575
A Urethra Franklin,
as I like to call it.

03:04.619 --> 03:06.360
I think I'm just gonna
punch him in the face.

03:06.403 --> 03:09.319
Well, that's not enough
for someone who stole your wife.

03:09.363 --> 03:11.365
You're right.
Yeah.

03:11.408 --> 03:13.410
You should destroy him.

03:13.454 --> 03:17.849
Tear his very life apart
piece by piece.

03:19.460 --> 03:21.157
And normally,
I'd help you do that,

03:21.201 --> 03:23.333
but I've picked up a new hobby
recently. Detective!

03:23.377 --> 03:25.248
REESE:
Detective?

03:25.292 --> 03:27.555
Yes. LAPD,
and I'm a consultant.

03:27.598 --> 03:29.383
You? You work with the police?

03:29.426 --> 03:31.863
Started a couple of weeks ago.
It's quite fun, actually.

03:31.907 --> 03:34.170
Hey, you know,
I've been trying to reach you.

03:34.214 --> 03:35.998
Detective, meet
my new friend. Uh...

03:36.041 --> 03:38.000
Uh, Reese.
Hi.

03:38.043 --> 03:40.785
Ah. Owner of the pieces.[Reese chuckles]

03:40.829 --> 03:42.004
Good to meet you.

03:42.047 --> 03:43.571
Uh, sorry to interrupt,
but I need

03:43.614 --> 03:46.878
my consultant to sober up
and join me at a crime scene.

03:46.922 --> 03:49.185
Oh, sounds lovely. All right.

03:49.229 --> 03:50.186
Nice meeting you.

03:50.230 --> 03:51.448
LUCIFER:
Yes. Oh.

03:51.492 --> 03:53.581
Good luck with the punishing.
[clicks tongue]

03:53.624 --> 03:56.584
REESE:
Hey, boss, I got something.

03:56.627 --> 03:58.368
Sleeping in your
office again?

03:58.412 --> 03:59.891
No, I'm working
on my new story.

03:59.935 --> 04:01.719
It's about
a shady nightclub owner.

04:01.763 --> 04:04.331
[laughs]
My top investigative reporter
wants me to approve a piece

04:04.374 --> 04:06.594
about overpriced booze
and go-go dancers?

04:06.637 --> 04:08.291
No, no, it's a con man.

04:08.335 --> 04:09.901
On paper, didn't even exist
five years ago.

04:09.945 --> 04:12.208
Tells everyone
he's the Devil.

04:12.252 --> 04:14.384
[scoffs] So he's a weirdo.
I don't see a story.

04:14.428 --> 04:15.690
He's consulting for the LAPD.

04:15.733 --> 04:18.258
I've got a bad feeling
this guy's up to no good.

04:18.301 --> 04:20.260
Remember the last time
I had a bad feeling?

04:20.303 --> 04:21.304
How can I forget your Pulitzer

04:21.348 --> 04:22.566
when you won't stop
reminding me?

04:22.610 --> 04:24.351
This son of a bitch
is hiding something.

04:24.394 --> 04:27.397
Who he is,
how he's exploiting the police.

04:27.441 --> 04:31.227
Whatever it is, the people
deserve to know the truth.

04:31.271 --> 04:32.837
Bringing this guy down,

04:32.881 --> 04:34.926
there wouldn't be a personal
reason behind it, would there?

04:34.970 --> 04:37.451
No. Of course not.

04:46.721 --> 04:48.113
Lucifer!

04:49.289 --> 04:52.248
Reese. Excuse me.

04:52.292 --> 04:53.945
What are you
doing here?

04:53.989 --> 04:56.121
Have you come to tell me about
the punishment you delivered?

04:56.165 --> 04:58.515
Probably not best to go into
detail in a police station.

04:58.559 --> 05:01.910
No. After we met last night,
I realized how...

05:01.953 --> 05:03.433
fascinating you are.

05:03.477 --> 05:05.435
Oh, well, I can't
argue with that.

05:05.479 --> 05:07.089
I'm a journalist
for the LA Telegraph.

05:07.132 --> 05:10.092
So I pitched my editor, and she
said I could do a piece on you.

05:10.135 --> 05:13.443
No. What, an entire
article dedicated to me?

05:13.487 --> 05:14.749
[laughs]

05:14.792 --> 05:16.359
Right. Well, let's
start with a talk.

05:16.403 --> 05:18.318
Gosh, this'll be fun.

05:22.365 --> 05:24.236
♪

05:31.461 --> 05:33.507
REESE: Can you tell me
about this guy, Lucifer?

05:33.550 --> 05:34.725
Yeah, he calls himself
"the Devil."

05:34.769 --> 05:36.423
He helped me out
with some gambling debts.

05:36.466 --> 05:37.598
Saved my life.

05:37.641 --> 05:38.947
Five years ago?

05:38.990 --> 05:41.602
I heard he was somewhere
terrible down south.

05:41.645 --> 05:43.125
He introduced me to my husband.

05:43.168 --> 05:44.126
And my horse.

05:44.169 --> 05:45.606
Maybe Florida?

05:45.649 --> 05:47.651
It's weird, but this is L.A.

05:49.566 --> 05:51.351
I don't know what to tell you.
I love the guy.

05:51.394 --> 05:52.569
Just love that guy.

05:52.613 --> 05:55.137
Everyone here
just loves Lucifer.

05:55.180 --> 05:56.573
I don't like Lucifer.

05:56.617 --> 05:58.749
Really?

05:58.793 --> 06:00.751
For starters,

06:00.795 --> 06:02.536
someone's been
stealing my pudding.

06:02.579 --> 06:04.581
And I don't think
it's a coincidence

06:04.625 --> 06:05.756
that it all started
when he showed up.

06:05.800 --> 06:07.192
No.

06:07.236 --> 06:09.369
And I'm not exactly in love
with the idea of my wife

06:09.412 --> 06:11.545
putting herself in danger
just so some club owner

06:11.588 --> 06:13.547
can have fun playing cop.

06:13.590 --> 06:15.331
You and Detective Decker
are married?

06:16.463 --> 06:18.247
We're separated.

06:18.290 --> 06:19.596
Oh, but still,

06:19.640 --> 06:20.554
that's got to be hard
watching them

06:20.597 --> 06:21.859
frolic around in front of you.

06:21.903 --> 06:24.645
I wouldn't say "frolic."

06:26.124 --> 06:27.430
[button clicks]

06:27.474 --> 06:29.650
Happy to keep this
off the record.

06:29.693 --> 06:33.175
Separated is not divorced.
There's still time.

06:33.218 --> 06:34.872
Excuse me. Hi.

06:34.916 --> 06:36.483
Uh, I know you.

06:36.526 --> 06:37.875
Aren't you the
guy from Lux?

06:37.919 --> 06:41.618
Reese Getty,
LA Telegraph.

06:41.662 --> 06:43.794
I'm here to write a story
about you and Lucifer.

06:43.838 --> 06:45.274
Oh, right.

06:45.317 --> 06:47.581
"Former B-movie Actress
Turned Detective

06:47.624 --> 06:49.278
Works With a Whack-Job
Consultant."

06:49.321 --> 06:50.627
Sounds about right.

06:50.671 --> 06:51.802
Yeah. No thanks.

06:51.846 --> 06:53.804
Detective Chloe Decker.
I did my research.

06:53.848 --> 06:57.591
Hot Tub High School,
your dad, I get it.

06:57.634 --> 06:59.593
You don't like the press.

06:59.636 --> 07:01.159
I don't have time for this.

07:01.203 --> 07:03.597
I have work to do that actually
contributes to society.

07:03.640 --> 07:05.599
I hate to be the one
to break it to you,

07:05.642 --> 07:07.470
but your lieutenant
and my editor are like this.

07:07.514 --> 07:09.254
I've been assigned to ride along
with you, Detective.

07:09.298 --> 07:11.692
So we can either
make this a pleasant experience,

07:11.735 --> 07:14.608
or we can do it the hard way.

07:14.651 --> 07:16.523
I'll pick the hard way.

07:17.654 --> 07:22.616
♪ Dancing in the fire

07:22.659 --> 07:26.358
♪ Yes, I'm dancing
in the fire ♪

07:26.402 --> 07:28.709
REESE: So, you just started
showing up at crime scenes,

07:28.752 --> 07:30.624
and eventually,
she let you work with her?

07:30.667 --> 07:32.495
LUCIFER:
Uh, more or less.

07:32.539 --> 07:34.541
Yeah. Um, excuse us.
[clears throat]

07:34.584 --> 07:36.891
No, no, no, just--
I'll stay out of your way.

07:36.934 --> 07:39.459
Just pretend
I'm not here.

07:39.502 --> 07:40.634
Here you go.

07:40.677 --> 07:42.723
What am I supposed
to do with these?

07:42.766 --> 07:44.681
Wear them... like
you always do.

07:44.725 --> 07:46.553
Oh, right, yeah.Mm-hmm.

07:46.596 --> 07:48.250
I don't.
Hi.

07:48.293 --> 07:49.730
DAN: Our victim's name
is Poppy Parker.

07:49.773 --> 07:51.514
She owns an organic
cosmetics line.

07:51.558 --> 07:54.648
Sort of a local celebrity
for all-natural skin care.

07:54.691 --> 07:56.519
CHLOE:
And, uh, what are all these?

07:56.563 --> 07:59.740
These are boobs.
Yes, I'd know them anywhere.

07:59.783 --> 08:01.655
C-cups to be precise.

08:01.698 --> 08:02.743
Oh, look at these.

08:02.786 --> 08:04.092
CHLOE:
Please don't...

08:04.135 --> 08:06.703
juggle the evidence, Lucifer.

08:06.747 --> 08:08.662
[Lucifer sighs]But it's fine if
he does, 'cause,

08:08.705 --> 08:10.011
you know,
they've already been processed.

08:10.054 --> 08:12.100
LUCIFER: They're called
"fun bags" for a reason.

08:12.143 --> 08:14.494
Actually, this one is
a calf implant, so you should

08:14.537 --> 08:15.669
have that,
Detective Douche.

08:15.712 --> 08:17.105
Looks like
you've been skipping leg day.

08:17.148 --> 08:20.195
Yeah, they're very, um,
low quality, actually.

08:20.238 --> 08:21.283
More outdated

08:21.326 --> 08:23.503
than Dan's flip phone.

08:23.546 --> 08:24.678
Don't think any

08:24.721 --> 08:26.157
surgeon in L.A. would use these.

08:26.201 --> 08:28.072
CHLOE: Hmm. Okay.
We'll look into it.

08:28.116 --> 08:30.335
Lucifer, he does this.

08:30.379 --> 08:33.904
He notices things
that normal people are too...

08:33.948 --> 08:35.732
normal to notice,

08:35.776 --> 08:36.907
but it, uh,

08:36.951 --> 08:38.561
has a tendency of paying off.

08:38.605 --> 08:39.693
It does.
[clicks tongue]

08:39.736 --> 08:40.824
DAN:
Why would he do this

08:40.868 --> 08:42.347
to someone
who values natural beauty?

08:42.391 --> 08:43.697
To punish her?

08:43.740 --> 08:45.568
Well, that is
a very good question, Daniel,

08:45.612 --> 08:46.917
but as an expert in punishment,

08:46.961 --> 08:48.005
because I'm the Devil...

08:48.049 --> 08:49.703
Hmm....this isn't punishment.

08:49.746 --> 08:50.573
This looks like

08:50.617 --> 08:52.923
someone making a statement.

08:52.967 --> 08:55.360
Well, maybe you're right.

08:55.404 --> 08:56.927
Needle mark on the lip,

08:56.971 --> 09:00.104
bruising around the injection.
This wasn't postmortem.

09:00.148 --> 09:02.716
Poppy wasn't as all-natural as
she wanted everyone to believe.

09:02.759 --> 09:04.065
She's a fraud.

09:05.414 --> 09:06.763
Someone wanted

09:06.807 --> 09:08.809
to reveal that the people
around her can't trust her.

09:08.852 --> 09:11.159
Ah.

09:11.202 --> 09:12.595
If that's the case,
I've seen this before.

09:12.639 --> 09:15.729
Oh, very good.
Go, Reese Lightning.

09:15.772 --> 09:17.121
[laughs]

09:17.165 --> 09:19.602
CHLOE:
So, Daniel Moore, vegan chef.

09:19.646 --> 09:21.343
Curiously found with
raw meat in his mouth.

09:21.386 --> 09:24.433
Ah. So vegans can't enjoy
a healthy sex life? [laughs]

09:25.608 --> 09:27.001
Tough crowd.

09:27.044 --> 09:28.742
Turns out, he
owns a cattle ranch

09:28.785 --> 09:31.135
in Montana, and the
environmentalist who was found

09:31.179 --> 09:33.834
drowned in jet fuel, he
actually owned a private plane.

09:33.877 --> 09:35.836
So, someone's killing
charlatans. Ah.

09:35.879 --> 09:37.751
The worst kind of scum.

09:37.794 --> 09:39.230
Next to boy bands.

09:39.274 --> 09:41.145
All three victims
had trace amounts of

09:41.189 --> 09:42.799
the exact same poison
in their system.

09:42.843 --> 09:44.584
Same profile, same M.O.

09:44.627 --> 09:46.760
This is a serial killer.

09:46.803 --> 09:48.762
Yes. The Completely Justified
Killer of Phonies.

09:48.805 --> 09:50.633
If that's what you name him,
I want credit.

09:50.677 --> 09:53.418
The first scene was
found over a month ago.

09:53.462 --> 09:54.811
Mm-hmm.

09:54.855 --> 09:56.770
The environmentalist,
a week ago.

09:56.813 --> 10:00.600
And Poppy here was found
just a few days later.

10:00.643 --> 10:03.385
I think the killer is
becoming more obsessed.

10:03.428 --> 10:05.169
He's accelerating
his timeline.

10:05.213 --> 10:07.998
We have to catch this guy
before anyone else dies.

10:08.042 --> 10:09.347
Why does Lucifer work with you?

10:12.220 --> 10:14.004
CHLOE:
I told you, it's an...

10:14.048 --> 10:15.658
unconventional partnership,
and it just...

10:15.702 --> 10:16.790
That's not it.

10:16.833 --> 10:18.313
What's he get out of it?

10:18.356 --> 10:21.925
You'll have to ask him.

10:39.682 --> 10:41.858
Hi, hon.

10:41.902 --> 10:45.035
I know you've been avoiding me.

10:45.079 --> 10:48.212
I mean, things have
been... off lately.

10:48.256 --> 10:52.477
But I want to try
and turn things around.

10:52.521 --> 10:55.524
Can we talk?

10:55.567 --> 10:58.048
I miss you.

11:08.755 --> 11:09.973
Leave Lucifer Morningstar alone.

11:11.758 --> 11:13.063
Or you'll be too dead
to regret it.

11:13.107 --> 11:14.717
I'm onto something, aren't I?

11:14.761 --> 11:16.023
You can't scare me off.

11:16.066 --> 11:17.633
I've been threatened
by worse than you.

11:18.895 --> 11:21.855
I guarantee you haven't.

11:21.898 --> 11:23.726
[grunts]

11:38.132 --> 11:39.524
Oh, Mr. Getty.

11:39.568 --> 11:41.352
I need you to look up
this address.

11:41.396 --> 11:42.876
Something shady

11:42.919 --> 11:44.878
going on here.O-Okay, but there's, uh...

11:44.921 --> 11:46.749
Got to be a drug den,
human trafficking...

11:46.793 --> 11:48.751
Mr. Getty, your wife's
in your office.

11:48.795 --> 11:49.926
Really?

11:49.970 --> 11:51.449
My wife?

11:53.582 --> 11:54.888
How do I look?

11:54.931 --> 11:56.890
Uh...

11:56.933 --> 11:58.239
[sighs]

12:04.158 --> 12:06.900
Reese.

12:06.943 --> 12:08.684
We need to talk.

12:11.731 --> 12:12.993
Linda.

12:13.036 --> 12:15.778
You look... wow.

12:17.867 --> 12:19.086
We should go to dinner.

12:19.129 --> 12:20.957
Our favorite Italian
place is still open.

12:21.001 --> 12:22.611
I'll make reservations.

12:22.654 --> 12:25.832
Reese, why are people in your
office calling me your wife?

12:25.875 --> 12:28.530
Because you are my wife.

12:28.573 --> 12:30.488
No. We're separated.

12:32.490 --> 12:34.666
It's been two years.

12:34.710 --> 12:36.668
That's actually why I'm here.

12:36.712 --> 12:40.847
I have been more
than patient, but it's time.

12:46.069 --> 12:48.942
Sign the divorce papers, please.

12:48.985 --> 12:53.337
[sighs] Is this because
you're seeing someone else?

12:53.381 --> 12:56.776
No. No, this isn't because
I'm seeing someone, Reese.

12:56.819 --> 13:00.954
You can't keep leaving me
voicemails like that.

13:00.997 --> 13:04.740
Things are not "off lately,"
things are over.

13:04.784 --> 13:06.786
You need to move on.

13:06.829 --> 13:09.136
I can't move on.

13:09.179 --> 13:11.573
Don't you know
how much I love you?

13:11.616 --> 13:14.837
You never give up.

13:14.881 --> 13:17.797
It's one of the reasons
I fell in love with you.

13:19.450 --> 13:21.235
But that was a long time ago.

13:21.278 --> 13:23.150
Not that long ago.

13:23.193 --> 13:24.586
This is classic denial.

13:24.629 --> 13:26.240
It's a self-defense mechanism
that you...

13:26.283 --> 13:27.458
Don't analyze me, Linda.

13:29.025 --> 13:30.592
Sorry.

13:34.030 --> 13:35.466
We're over.

13:37.033 --> 13:39.427
Sign them.

13:41.995 --> 13:45.389
I'm working on something,
and I need a little more time.

13:45.433 --> 13:49.176
Why? Nothing you're working on
is gonna change anything.

13:49.219 --> 13:50.830
24 hours, that's all
I'm asking for.

13:50.873 --> 13:53.833
Okay, if I do...

13:53.876 --> 13:56.139
you'll finally sign the papers?

13:56.183 --> 13:57.880
I promise.

14:13.678 --> 14:15.898
Hey. Did you find anything
about that address yet?

14:15.942 --> 14:17.900
It's a known hot spot
for trading stolen goods.

14:17.944 --> 14:19.206
I knew he was up to something.

14:19.249 --> 14:20.860
Fencing? Smuggling? Or worse?

14:20.903 --> 14:21.991
Well, I can do some research
on the building.

