29:09.051 --> 29:10.879
♪ Are you ready
for the Devil, man?

29:10.923 --> 29:13.055
♪ Are you ready for the Devil?

29:23.631 --> 29:25.502
♪ Ha-ha, ha-ha, ha-ha

29:34.033 --> 29:36.078
LUCIFER [echoing]: You're lucky
the detective isn't here.

29:36.122 --> 29:37.819
You'd be cleaning my blood
out of the couch.

29:37.863 --> 29:40.822
♪ No mercy, no mercy

29:43.694 --> 29:46.001
♪ Are you ready
for the Devil, man? ♪

29:46.045 --> 29:48.743
♪ Are you ready for
the Devil? ♪

29:48.787 --> 29:51.267
♪ Are you ready
for the Devil, man? ♪

29:54.662 --> 29:55.794
[knocks]

30:05.064 --> 30:07.283
Alvin Kapitski?Yeah.

30:07.327 --> 30:09.459
Registered on the
LA Telegraphweb site

30:09.503 --> 30:11.331
as "TruthDog21"?

30:11.374 --> 30:14.073
I wanted to ask you
a few questions

30:14.116 --> 30:15.857
about some comments
that you posted

30:15.901 --> 30:18.207
on some stories we ran
about Poppy Parker

30:18.251 --> 30:19.426
and Daniel Moore.

30:19.469 --> 30:22.037
Okay.

30:22.081 --> 30:23.517
Okay.

30:25.736 --> 30:28.522
I knew this day would come.

30:28.565 --> 30:30.219
I'll surrender quietly.

30:30.263 --> 30:31.351
Oh, no.

30:31.394 --> 30:32.918
I'm not a cop.

30:32.961 --> 30:34.876
I'm a reporter.

30:34.920 --> 30:36.922
I just want to
talk to you.

30:38.924 --> 30:41.230
You're here to
do a story on me?

30:41.274 --> 30:44.755
Well, my job is to
dig up the truth.

30:44.799 --> 30:47.280
Expose people for
who they really are.

30:47.323 --> 30:49.064
And once I saw your work,

30:49.108 --> 30:50.979
I-I realized that

30:51.023 --> 30:53.068
you were just doing
the same thing.
Yeah.

30:53.112 --> 30:54.635
Yeah, I was.

30:56.550 --> 30:58.073
I'm back on my meds now.

30:58.117 --> 31:00.162
I'm trying to be good.
It's hard, but I'm trying.

31:00.206 --> 31:02.077
I'm trying, I'm trying.I get it.

31:02.121 --> 31:04.993
It's just, I met this guy

31:05.037 --> 31:06.690
recently.

31:06.734 --> 31:09.519
Biggest fraud
I'd ever encountered.

31:09.563 --> 31:11.304
Yeah?

31:11.347 --> 31:13.915
I tried to expose him,

31:13.959 --> 31:16.831
show everybody the liar
that he really is.

31:18.137 --> 31:19.268
What happened?

31:19.312 --> 31:21.270
He won.

31:21.314 --> 31:24.795
They always do,
don't they?

31:27.146 --> 31:29.017
Unless someone does something.

31:36.329 --> 31:38.157
What's his name?

31:38.200 --> 31:40.986
[dance music playing]

31:43.162 --> 31:45.207
Hi.

31:45.251 --> 31:46.774
Thanks for coming.
Hey,

31:46.817 --> 31:48.994
you're helping me,
so thanks.

31:49.037 --> 31:52.171
Although I have no idea
why we had to meet here.

31:52.214 --> 31:53.128
Those them?

31:53.172 --> 31:55.348
Yeah, uh,

31:55.391 --> 31:57.350
all the redacted
comments.

31:57.393 --> 32:00.309
♪

32:00.353 --> 32:03.095
Uh, but first,

32:03.138 --> 32:04.879
I never did get
to interview you.

32:04.923 --> 32:07.360
You know, you really
had me fooled.

32:07.403 --> 32:08.970
Thought you were different.

32:09.014 --> 32:11.451
Fine, ask away.

32:11.494 --> 32:13.018
What do you think
Lucifer gets

32:13.061 --> 32:14.454
out of this partnership?

32:16.238 --> 32:17.544
CHLOE:
You already asked me that.

32:17.587 --> 32:20.547
Uh, but you never answered.

32:20.590 --> 32:24.812
Um... I think,

32:24.855 --> 32:25.900
a long time ago,

32:25.944 --> 32:28.163
somebody wronged Lucifer.

32:28.207 --> 32:29.469
I think he avoided
dealing with it,

32:29.512 --> 32:31.210
and he hides

32:31.253 --> 32:33.081
behind the partying

32:33.125 --> 32:36.258
and the women and the drinking,
and who knows what else.

32:36.302 --> 32:37.999
And with the LAPD,

32:38.043 --> 32:40.610
working on each case,
it gives him an opportunity

32:40.654 --> 32:42.786
to right those wrongs,
to fight back.

32:42.830 --> 32:44.397
[chuckles]:
Oh.

32:44.440 --> 32:46.181
You think that's funny?

32:46.225 --> 32:48.183
Uh, no, no.
I'm sorry.

32:48.227 --> 32:50.707
REESE:
I just think, uh,

32:50.751 --> 32:52.405
you give him more credit

32:52.448 --> 32:54.146
than he deserves.

32:54.189 --> 32:55.712
Well, I don't think
you give him enough.

32:55.756 --> 32:57.584
♪ After the rain

32:57.627 --> 33:01.196
♪ Washes away our sins

33:01.240 --> 33:06.854
♪ They never said that
love is a twisted game ♪

33:06.897 --> 33:09.248
♪ And no one ever wins

33:09.291 --> 33:12.642
You may be right.

33:12.686 --> 33:14.427
♪ We've been here before

33:14.470 --> 33:16.646
Thanks, Detective.

33:16.690 --> 33:19.432
♪ You want something more

33:19.475 --> 33:21.390
♪ Lover, best friend

33:21.434 --> 33:23.392
♪ My worst enemy

33:23.436 --> 33:25.046
♪ You know I won't...

33:25.090 --> 33:26.395
CHLOE:
Um... [clears throat]

33:26.439 --> 33:27.831
these, uh...

33:27.875 --> 33:29.268
these look incomplete.

33:29.311 --> 33:30.747
[woman screams]

33:30.791 --> 33:33.098
WOMAN:
Help! Help, help!

33:34.273 --> 33:36.275
Help! Help!
Help! Help!

33:36.318 --> 33:38.103
[crowd murmuring]

33:44.196 --> 33:45.197
She's dead.

33:45.240 --> 33:47.199
[mouths]

33:47.242 --> 33:49.288
CHLOE:
What happened?

33:52.291 --> 33:54.771
ELLA:
Yeah, you were right.

33:54.815 --> 33:56.164
Looks like the same poison

33:56.208 --> 33:57.470
that was used by that
serial killer

33:57.513 --> 33:58.775
you guys were after.

33:58.819 --> 34:01.474
They did this under
my own roof.

34:01.517 --> 34:02.823
My home.

34:07.915 --> 34:09.264
How-how could the killer
be here

34:09.308 --> 34:12.093
the exact same time we were?

34:12.137 --> 34:15.053
Must be something,
must...

34:17.011 --> 34:18.317
It must be you.

34:18.360 --> 34:20.797
What?
What do you mean?

34:20.841 --> 34:22.321
He was here for you.

34:22.364 --> 34:24.149
He must have figured out
that you were gonna

34:24.192 --> 34:26.325
pass over information
about him.

34:26.368 --> 34:28.109
I'm so sorry.

34:28.153 --> 34:29.328
This is... this is all my fault.

34:29.371 --> 34:31.112
I'm to blame.
I put you in danger.

34:31.156 --> 34:33.723
No, no, no,
this is not your fault.

34:33.767 --> 34:36.074
There's only one person
who's to blame for this.

34:38.989 --> 34:39.990
Yeah.

34:49.783 --> 34:51.263
I'm in no mood for
whatever it is.

34:51.306 --> 34:52.742
You.

34:54.744 --> 34:56.572
This is all your fault.

35:02.230 --> 35:05.015
You ruined my life.
You drove me to do things

35:05.059 --> 35:06.016
I never would've done.

35:06.060 --> 35:07.757
And now...

35:07.801 --> 35:09.716
there's a dead girl
down there because of you.

35:09.759 --> 35:12.153
What is it with you humans?

35:12.197 --> 35:14.329
Huh? Always blaming me.

35:14.373 --> 35:18.203
I never make any of you
do anything.

35:18.246 --> 35:19.682
That's not true.

35:19.726 --> 35:20.727
You trick us

35:20.770 --> 35:21.945
into sin,

35:21.989 --> 35:23.338
damnation.

35:23.382 --> 35:25.384
[sighs]

35:25.427 --> 35:28.038
I have a story for you,
reporter.

35:29.997 --> 35:33.000
One I've never told
a human soul before.

35:33.043 --> 35:36.134
I take no part
in who goes to Hell.

35:36.177 --> 35:37.613
Then who does?

35:37.657 --> 35:39.137
You humans.

35:39.180 --> 35:41.182
[chuckles]
You send yourselves.

35:41.226 --> 35:43.750
Driven down by your own guilt.

35:43.793 --> 35:45.708
Forcing yourselves

35:45.752 --> 35:48.233
to relive your sins
over and over.

35:48.276 --> 35:50.104
And the best part...

35:51.366 --> 35:54.021
the doors aren't locked.

35:54.064 --> 35:55.849
You could leave anytime.

35:55.892 --> 35:57.329
It says something

35:57.372 --> 35:59.331
that no one ever does,
doesn't it?

35:59.374 --> 36:01.159
No.

36:01.202 --> 36:02.421
You're to blame.

36:02.464 --> 36:05.380
I am responsible for
a lot of things, Reese,

36:05.424 --> 36:06.555
but not your soul,

36:06.599 --> 36:07.991
not your actions,

36:08.035 --> 36:11.212
and not whoever killed
that poor girl downstairs.

36:11.256 --> 36:13.345
Eh, you...

36:13.388 --> 36:15.738
you have to be.

36:15.782 --> 36:16.870
Otherwise...

36:21.918 --> 36:24.921
Hurting me is not what you
really want to do, is it?

36:28.011 --> 36:29.361
What are you doing to me?

36:29.404 --> 36:32.407
Oh, you're a complicated one,
aren't you, Reese?

36:32.451 --> 36:33.365
Strong.

36:33.408 --> 36:35.193
Tell me...

36:36.368 --> 36:39.371
what do you truly desire?

36:39.414 --> 36:41.286
I...

36:44.289 --> 36:46.595
I just want Linda to love me.

36:46.639 --> 36:49.207
[knife drops]

36:49.250 --> 36:50.773
You're still in love
with your ex?

36:50.817 --> 36:51.992
What about your wife?

36:52.035 --> 36:53.341
She is my wife.

36:55.300 --> 36:57.389
She'll always be my wife.

36:57.432 --> 36:59.304
So... hold on,

36:59.347 --> 37:01.784
that-that sleazy,
piece of garbage, that...

37:01.828 --> 37:04.309
[chuckles]
that was me?

37:04.352 --> 37:06.485
[laughs]

37:06.528 --> 37:08.922
It was me.

37:08.965 --> 37:10.402
The way she looks at you.

37:10.445 --> 37:11.403
Ah...

37:11.446 --> 37:13.361
She cares for you.

37:13.405 --> 37:16.408
How'd you do that?

37:16.451 --> 37:21.804
How did you convince her
that the Devil, of all people...

37:21.848 --> 37:23.241
was good?

37:23.284 --> 37:26.461
I don't know.

37:26.505 --> 37:29.856
I just...
showed her my true self.

37:29.899 --> 37:33.381
But how could she
accept you after that?

37:33.425 --> 37:37.646
Well, maybe she did...
because of that.

37:37.690 --> 37:39.300
[chuckles]

37:39.344 --> 37:40.780
Hmm.

37:42.564 --> 37:44.479
Before you say anything,
hear me out.

37:44.523 --> 37:45.959
There's nothing
you can say.

37:46.002 --> 37:47.352
I was a bad husband.

37:47.395 --> 37:48.657
Put my work
above everything,

37:48.701 --> 37:50.180
above us.

37:50.224 --> 37:51.399
Our marriage failing

37:51.443 --> 37:52.661
was all my fault.

37:52.705 --> 37:53.706
And I'm sorry.

37:58.537 --> 37:59.929
You deserved better.

38:02.541 --> 38:04.804
Well, if we're...
if we're being honest...

38:07.023 --> 38:10.331
it wasn't all
your fault.

38:10.375 --> 38:11.767
I wasn't perfect either.

38:13.160 --> 38:16.076
Truth is...

38:16.119 --> 38:18.557
neither one of us could be
what the other one needed.

38:20.036 --> 38:21.124
That's why it's good

38:21.168 --> 38:23.518
that we're going
our separate ways.

38:23.562 --> 38:25.999
But, Linda, no, no, I...

38:26.042 --> 38:29.219
I thought me opening up
would bring us closer.

38:29.263 --> 38:32.005
Like it did with
you and Lucifer.

38:32.048 --> 38:33.659
Reese,

38:33.702 --> 38:35.225
that's not how this works.

38:36.792 --> 38:38.664
You forgave the Devil.

38:38.707 --> 38:40.143
Why can't you forgive me?

38:40.187 --> 38:41.536
[scoffs]

38:41.580 --> 38:43.582
You know, for a second,

38:43.625 --> 38:47.542
I thought that you were honestly
taking responsibility.

38:47.586 --> 38:50.502
But it's always the same
with you, over and over.

38:50.545 --> 38:53.505
So determined, you never listen,
never learn.

38:53.548 --> 38:54.506
Do you know
how much I love you?

38:54.549 --> 38:56.508
The things that
I've done for you.

38:56.551 --> 38:58.031
I went up against the Devil.

38:58.074 --> 39:00.599
I risked everything getting
involved with a serial killer.

39:00.642 --> 39:02.122
A poor girl got killed!

39:02.165 --> 39:03.732
Wait, what?

39:03.776 --> 39:05.168
I-I can explain...

39:05.212 --> 39:06.169
Reese, what have you done?

39:06.213 --> 39:07.562
No, it-it wasn't my fault.

39:07.606 --> 39:08.737
I'm calling the police.
No.

39:08.781 --> 39:09.912
It was an accident.

39:09.956 --> 39:12.001
I-I didn't mean for
any of this to happen.

39:13.481 --> 39:14.613
Reese.
Stop.

39:14.656 --> 39:16.528
Let me explain.Reese, let go of me.

39:16.571 --> 39:17.529
Reese.
No, no!

39:17.572 --> 39:20.096
No!
Reese, no!

39:22.664 --> 39:24.623
Oh, God.
I'm sorry.

39:29.062 --> 39:31.151
You're right.

39:31.194 --> 39:32.631
Call Detective Decker.

39:32.674 --> 39:34.633
Tell them they can
find me at my office.

39:34.676 --> 39:38.767
I'll give them everything
that I have on Kapitski.

39:38.811 --> 39:41.074
And I'll turn myself in.

39:41.117 --> 39:42.292
I'm sorry.

39:45.687 --> 39:47.994
You were right.

39:48.037 --> 39:49.430
Let me make this right.

39:49.474 --> 39:51.606
Good-bye, Reese.

40:01.486 --> 40:02.617
[sighs]

40:04.227 --> 40:05.359
[sighs]

40:09.624 --> 40:11.017
[gags]

40:14.586 --> 40:17.980
KAPITSKI: You sent me
to kill the wrong man.

40:18.024 --> 40:20.243
Lucifer wasn't a fraud.[glass drops]

40:20.287 --> 40:21.636
He's an honest man.

40:21.680 --> 40:22.768
As honest as they come.

40:22.811 --> 40:25.814
No, no, the fraud is you!

40:25.858 --> 40:28.469
[gags]
Reporter
lying to people.

40:28.513 --> 40:30.906
A coward trying to get another
man to do his dirty work.

40:30.950 --> 40:32.604
You're the one
who deserves to go next.

40:35.128 --> 40:36.608
And now you will.

40:36.651 --> 40:38.653
[laughs]

40:38.697 --> 40:40.046
What are you laughing about?

40:40.089 --> 40:42.048
I caught you.

40:42.091 --> 40:43.658
[siren chirps]

40:43.702 --> 40:44.616
Crap!

40:44.659 --> 40:46.531
[both grunting]Let go! No!

40:46.574 --> 40:47.662
[wheezes]

40:51.840 --> 40:55.061
Stay down.[handcuffs tighten]

40:55.104 --> 40:58.499
[Reese wheezing]

41:02.677 --> 41:05.680
[Reese gasping]

41:05.724 --> 41:07.552
Oh, Reesey.

41:07.595 --> 41:09.510
You laying down on the job?

41:11.556 --> 41:13.253
Don't tell me, asthma.

41:13.296 --> 41:15.342
That...

41:15.385 --> 41:17.475
or the poison I drank.

41:18.780 --> 41:20.565
[Lucifer scoffs]

41:20.608 --> 41:23.829
Well...

41:23.872 --> 41:25.700
you didn't drink all of it.

41:25.744 --> 41:26.701
[siren approaching]

41:26.745 --> 41:29.617
I set things right.

41:29.661 --> 41:33.403
Maybe this will
turn things around...

41:33.447 --> 41:34.535
with Linda.

41:34.579 --> 41:36.494
[wheezing continues]

41:47.809 --> 41:49.202
[inhales deeply]

41:58.603 --> 42:02.389
Welcome back to the land
of the living, Mr. Getty.

42:10.702 --> 42:13.531
What...

42:13.574 --> 42:14.706
what happened?

42:14.749 --> 42:17.230
Just a little brush with death.

42:17.273 --> 42:19.711
You had us worried there
for a while.

42:19.754 --> 42:21.147
[groans softly]

42:24.759 --> 42:25.760
Is my wife here?

42:26.935 --> 42:28.023
No.

42:29.416 --> 42:31.244
I'm sorry, you haven't
had any visitors.

42:32.419 --> 42:34.900
Well...

42:34.943 --> 42:36.989
we have been having
some trouble lately.

42:39.818 --> 42:41.341
But you know what?

42:41.384 --> 42:43.256
Second chance on life.

42:43.299 --> 42:45.127
Maybe it's not too late
to turn things around.

42:45.171 --> 42:47.086
♪ Hey!

42:54.223 --> 42:55.964
♪ Hey!♪♪ I'm sick of seeing

42:56.008 --> 42:58.706
♪ Your face so much

42:58.750 --> 43:00.447
♪ Television's off

43:00.490 --> 43:03.145
♪ But you won't shut up

43:03.189 --> 43:06.758
♪ Hey!♪♪ Oh, oh

43:06.801 --> 43:08.063
♪ Give it up

43:15.636 --> 43:16.594
♪ Hey!♪
